{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.25",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 25,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 25 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:1",
      "text": "These are the miscellaneous instructions of Solomon, which the friends of Ezekias king of Judea copied out.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:2",
      "text": "The glory of God conceals a matter: but the glory of a king honours business.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:3",
      "text": "Heaven is high, and earth is deep, and a king's heart is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:4",
      "text": "Beat the drossy silver, and it shall be made entirely pure. Slay the ungodly from before the king, and his throne shall prosper in righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:6",
      "text": "Be not boastful in the presence of the king, and remain not in the places of princes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:7",
      "text": "for it is better for thee that it should be said, Come up to me, than that one should humble thee in the presence of the prince; speak of that which thine eyes have seen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:8",
      "text": "Get not suddenly into a quarrel, lest thou repent at last.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:9",
      "text": "Whenever thy friend shall reproach thee, retreat backward, despise him not;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:10",
      "text": "lest thy friend continue to reproach thee, so thy quarrel and enmity shall not depart, but shall be to thee like death. 10a Favour and friendship set a man free, which do thou keep for thyself, lest thou be made liable to reproach; but take heed to thy ways peaceably.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:11",
      "text": "As a golden apple in a necklace of sardius, so is it to speak a wise word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:12",
      "text": "In an ear-ring of gold a precious sardius is also set; so is a wise word to an obedient ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:13",
      "text": "As a fall of snow in the time of harvest is good against heat, so a faithful messenger refreshes those that send him; for he helps the souls of his employers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:14",
      "text": "As winds and clouds and rains are most evident objects, so is he that boasts of a false gift.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:15",
      "text": "In long-suffering is prosperity to kings, and a soft tongue breaks the bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:16",
      "text": "Having found honey, eat only what is enough, lest haply thou be filled, and vomit it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:17",
      "text": "Enter sparingly into thy friend's house, lest he be satiated with thy company, and hate thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:18",
      "text": "As a club, and a dagger, and a pointed arrow, so also is a man who bears false witness against his friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:19",
      "text": "The way of the wicked and the foot of the transgressor shall perish in an evil day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:20",
      "text": "As vinegar is bad for a sore, so trouble befalling the body afflicts the heart. 20a As a moth in a garment, and a worm in wood, so the grief of a man hurts the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:21",
      "text": "If thine enemy hunger, feed him; if he thirst, give him drink;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:22",
      "text": "for so doing thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee with good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:23",
      "text": "The north wind raises clouds; so an impudent face provokes the tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:24",
      "text": "It is better to dwell on a corner of the roof, than with a railing woman in an open house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:25",
      "text": "As cold water is agreeable to a thirsting soul, so is a good message from a land far off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:26",
      "text": "As if one should stop a well, and corrupt a spring of water, so is it unseemly for a righteous man to fall before an ungodly man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:27",
      "text": "It is not good to eat much honey; but it is right to honour venerable sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.25.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:28",
      "text": "As a city whose walls are broken down, and which is unfortified, so is a man who does anything without counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
